<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-0226 </DOCNO><TEXT>A simple model for a reactor accident is reviewed and an explicit time-dependentsolution of the nonlinear equations is obtained. This shows that fora negative reactivity coefficient, the shutdown approaches the operatingcentre infinitely slowly, but that for positive coefficient, the statevariables become infinite at a finite escape time. These explicit resultsmay serve to introduce nonlinear dynamics.</TEXT></DOC>